2. NEW GAME

When you start a new game you will  be asked to choose a team from the
forty league sides. Once you have  chosen  your team you will be asked
to type in your own name. You don`t have to use your own name, you can
be anyone you want.  You  could  go  for  Bernard  Rooney, a legend in
Greenock, leading  Morton  to  glory  in  the  1977-78  Scottish First
Division, or Alex Ferguson another  Scottish  legend who took Aberdeen
to the top winning numerous  domestic  honours and even European glory
in the early 1980`s.  I  believe  he`s  doing  okay  somewhere down in
England.

Once you have passed that stage,  you  can then select which strip you
want your team to wear. There are ten different strips to choose from.

Clearing that hurdle takes you to the Main Menu.

