3. MAIN MENU

At the top of this screen you  will  see your name, your team name and
how much cash you have. At the bottom, you will see what division your
in, the season number (i.e season 1, 2..etc) and the week number.

You will have the following choice:

                                  A. LEAGUE TABLE
                                  B. FINANCES
                                  C. HISTORY
                                  D. SQUAD
                                  E. TRANSFERS
                                  F. SAVE GAME
                                  G. STADIUM
                                  H. FIXTURES
                                  I. NEXT MATCH

3A LEAGUE TABLE.

Shows the current position  of  the  teams,  games  played, won, lost,
drawn, goals for, goals against, and points won.

If two or more teams have the same number of points then the team with
the better goal difference will  take  priority.  If two or more teams
have the same goal difference then the  team who has scored more goals
will take priority.

Selecting EXIT will take you back to the Main Menu.


3B FINANCES.

This screen displays all cash coming in and going out of the club.

* Gate Receipts *
The home team keeps all  cash,  except  cup  games when money is split
both ways.

* Club Wages *
Total weekly bill of players wages.

* Transfers *
Total of transfer money coming in and going out.

* Sponsors *
When   winning a trophy or  being  beaten,  you will receive a payment
from the trophy sponsors. Payment depends on which round you exit. The
further your cup run the more cash.

* TV Deals *
Every cup game is televised. Payment  depends on which round and which
division your team is in.

* Merchandise *
Total of all club merchandise sold in the week. Usually more when your
playing at home.

* Improvements *
Total for improvements made to the stadium.

* Club Bills *
Total of the day to day running, stewarding, catering etc.

All details shown are for  the  previous  weeks activities. Totals for
incoming and outgoing cash are also given together with +/- profit.

On this screen you can choose from the following:

                              FINANCES
                              PLAYERS WAGES
                              GATES
                              EXIT

* Finances *
Takes you back to the Finances screen.

* Players Wages *
Lists all current team members and their weekly wages.

* Gates *
Lists all teams played, the venue and attendances.

* Exit *
Takes you back to the Main Menu.


3C HISTORY.

Displays all your achievements:

                               FA CUPS WON
                               FA FINALS REACHED
                               LEAGUE CUPS WON
                               LEAGUE CUP FINALS REACHED
                               PREMIER LEAGUES WON
                               FIRST DIVISION LEAGUES WON
                               SECOND DIVISION LEAGUES WON
                               THIRD DIVISION LEAGUES WON
                               TOTAL GAMES PLAYED
                               TOTAL GAMES WON
                               TOTAL GAMES LOST
                               TOTAL GAMES DRAWN
                               SEASONS PLAYED


3D SQUAD.

Displayed on this screen is your current squad, here you will see:

Players name, players position (G, D, M or A), players rating (1-10),
goals scored and the players value.

You can have up to  eighteen  players  in  your squad. Eleven players,
three substitutes and four reserves.

To swap any player about, select  the  players  name, his name will be
high-lighted. Now select another player and they will swap places.

The following formations are available:

4-4-2, 3-5-2, 3-4-3, 5-3-2, 5-2-3 or 3-6-1.

The teams rating is calculated  on  the  formation.  Trying to use any
other formation will result in a weakened side.

You also have the following choices:

                                    EDIT
                                    TEAM INFO
                                    INJURIES
                                    TRAINING
                                    SUSPENSIONS
                                    SELL PLAYER
                                    EXIT

EDIT.

To edit a players name, select this option then select a players name.
You will now be able to  enter  a  new  name  for the player using the
keyboard.

TEAM INFO.

This displays details of your next  opponents.  You will be shown both
yours and their league statistics. Also  given  are your own and their
totals for strength in attack, midfield, defence and goalkeeping.

INJURIES.

If a player is  injured,  his  name  will  be  shown together with the
number of weeks he will be  out.  This  information will also be shown
after every match. If a player is injured  his position (G, D, M or A)
will change to I.

TRAINING.

This is a vital part  of  management.  If  your  team are not training
their abilities will be affected.

To put a player on training,  select this option. The current training
for each player will  be  shown.  Select  the  players  name and their
training will change.

Each player can have  training  on  an  individual skill like passing,
control or shooting. Goalkeepers can have handling or diving, etc.

SUSPENSIONS.

If a player is suspended,  his  name  will  be shown together with the
number of weeks he will be  out.  This  information will also be shown
after every match. If a player is  suspended  his position (G, D, M or
A) will change to S.

SELL PLAYER.

If you decide to  sell  a  player,  select  this  option. Now select a
player and any offers will be shown.  If  you want to accept an offer,
select the teams name and the  player  will  be  off. To turn down all
offers, select decline.

EXIT.

Takes you back to the Main Menu.


3E TRANSFERS.

If you feel you have to strengthen your  squad this is the place to go
to. This screen will display all players available to buy. The details
shown are:

Players name, players ability  rating,  the  division  he is currently
playing in and his value.

To bid for a player select buy, then select the players name. You will
then be shown another menu to  choose  your  bid. To increase your bid
select +£100. To decrease your  bid  select  -£100. Once you are happy
with your bid press the right mouse  button to enter the bid. Next you
will be shown a list of  offers  from  any other interested teams. The
selling team will accept the highest offer.

You can keep buying players until your  cash  runs out or there are no
more players or you have a full squad.

Selecting EXIT will take you back to the Main Menu.


3F SAVE GAME.

Only available in the full version.


3G STADIUM.

On this screen you can increase  your  stadiums capacity or change the
ticket prices. The stadium name and  current capacity will be shown at
the top of the screen.

CAPACITY.

When this option has been  selected  you  will  be given the choice of
increasing the capacity by 5000.  This  usually takes about five weeks
to complete.

TICKETS.

This option allows you to increase/decrease the price of your tickets.

The average ticket prices are as follows:

Premier League :
north & south stands - £14   east & west stands - £13.

Division One   :
north & south stands - £11   east & west stands - £9.

Division Two   :
north & south stands - £8    east & west stands - £6.

Division Three :
north & south stands - £5    east & west stands - £3.

Selecting + increases the ticket  price  and selecting - decreases the
price.

If you charge to much  the  fans  will  stay  away, costing you money.
Although it is possible to increase  the  price and punish those stay-
away fans during a wicked cup run.

Also, if you  charge  much  less  than  the  standard  prices you will
probably have a bigger attendance.

Selecting EXIT takes you to the Main Menu.


3H FIXTURES.

Details the seasons fixtures  for  your  team  together with venue and
which tournament (i.e League, FA Cup or League Cup). Also shown is the
results of any games that have been played.

Selecting EXIT takes you back to the Main Menu.


3I NEXT MATCH.

Listen to the buzz of the crowd as the teams kick off!

Your fixture is shown at the top of the screen along with the time. At
the bottom half of the screen are the rest of your leagues matches and
their current score.

During the game you will be  shown  shots at goal, penalties etc. Hear
the crowd roar  as  your  star  striker  runs  through  and smashes an
unstoppable shot into  the  back  of  the  net  and  bows  to take the
applause!.

To make a substitution during  the  game,  press the mouse button. You
will then  be  presented  with  your  first  eleven  players  and  any
remaining substitutes. To change  a  player,  select  the  name of the
player you wish to remove. His name will be highlighted. Then select a
substitute. They will then swap places.

Selecting EXIT takes you back to the match.

At the end of ninety minutes you  will  be shown the attendance of the
match then the final results.

If you are playing in a cup match and the scores are equal, extra time
will be played. If the scores are still equal at the end of extra time
the teams will enter a penalty shoot-out.

Listen to the crowd roar as a player misses his kick!

The teams will take five penalties each. If after these five kicks the
scores are still the same the teams will play sudden death penalties.

After the  match  is  finished  you  will  be  shown  any  injuries or
suspension to your players. Then you will be taken to the Main Menu.

